                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 SM 511/390: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-15T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 15, 1942—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>435. Your 760, May 12, 1 p.m. Talbot Smith, assigned Consul at Asmara, has been
                    instructed to visit Addis Ababa some time after arrival at his post in order to
                    request exequatur covering Ethiopian territory. You may convey this to Tesfaye
                    in your discretion.</p>
                <p>For your confidential information, Smith has also been requested to report upon
                    the desirability of reestablishing our diplomatic mission in Ethiopia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
